Job Title: Telemedicine Nurse, Anesthesia Specialist, and Health Officer

Job Description:

SAINT PAUL'S HOSPITAL MILLENNIUM MEDICAL COLLEGE, the first institution in Ethiopia to deploy telemedicine technology, is currently seeking qualified individuals to join our innovative telemedicine team in the positions of Nurse, Anesthesia Specialist, and Health Officer. These roles are instrumental in providing remote healthcare services and driving the effective implementation of telemedicine technology within our organization.

Responsibilities:

Nurse:

  • remote patient assessments and consultations using telemedicine technology, leveraging our cutting-edge telemedicine platform.
  • Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams to develop and implement patient care plans tailored to remote healthcare delivery.
  • Administer medications, treatments, and procedures as prescribed, ensuring high-quality care for patients accessing telemedicine services.
  • Maintain accurate and up-to-date patient records in our advanced electronic health records (EHR) systems, contributing to seamless continuity of care.
  • Participate in telemedicine training sessions for medical staff, sharing expertise and insights to enhance proficiency in telemedicine practices.
  • Provide compassionate and patient-centered care to individuals accessing telemedicine services, embodying our commitment to excellence in remote healthcare delivery

Anesthesia Specialist:

  • Provide expert anesthesia support during telemedicine procedures, leveraging our state-of-the-art telemedicine infrastructure to ensure safe and effective patient care.
  • Collaborate closely with surgeons, physicians, and other healthcare providers to optimize patient outcomes in remote medical interventions.
  • Monitor patient vital signs and respond promptly to any changes or complications, utilizing telemedicine technology to provide timely interventions.
  • Maintain proficiency in anesthesia techniques and protocols, contributing to the development and implementation of tele-anesthesia best practices.
  • Contribute to the ongoing advancement of telemedicine anesthesia practices, driving innovation and excellence in remote anesthesia delivery.

Health Officer:

  • Oversee the health and safety of telemedicine operations at SAINT PAUL'S HOSPITAL MILLENNIUM MEDICAL COLLEGE, ensuring compliance with telemedicine regulations and standards.
  • Develop and implement policies and procedures related to telemedicine services, drawing upon our extensive experience as pioneers in telemedicine deployment in Ethiopia.
  • Provide guidance and support to staff members on telemedicine-related issues, leveraging our organization's unique expertise in remote healthcare delivery.
  • Collaborate with IT professionals to address technical aspects of telemedicine implementation, contributing to the ongoing optimization of our telemedicine infrastructure.
  • Monitor telemedicine outcomes and identify opportunities for continuous improvement, driving excellence in remote healthcare delivery at our institution.

Requirements:

  • Bachelor's degree in Nursing with specialization in Anesthesia for the Anesthesia Specialist role. For the Nurse and Health Officer roles, a Bachelor's degree in Nursing, Public Health, or a related field is required.
  • Current nursing license.
  • 0 year experience.
  • Strong understanding of telemedicine technology and its application in healthcare settings, with a demonstrated commitment to excellence in remote healthcare delivery.
  • Excellent communication, teamwork, and problem-solving skills, with a passion for driving innovation and excellence in telemedicine.
  • Ability to work effectively in a remote setting and collaborate with multidisciplinary teams, embodying our organization's values of collaboration and patient-centered care.
  • Dedication to providing high-quality patient care and promoting the well-being of individuals accessing telemedicine services, reflecting our organization's mission to deliver accessible, equitable, and compassionate healthcare to all.

Salary:

As per company scale

Benefits:

Competitive benefits package including health insurance, retirement plans, and opportunities for professional development.
